            <title>[THRIFT-2788] Java client and server does not enable tcp keep alive.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-2788</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Both client and server sockets in Java were not enable tcp keepalive.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is important for reap dead tcp connections. If not enabled, the process can not be notified appropriately while remote peer crashed or connection interrupted.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
